Plan:
- Provide a self-contained Python script that fetches the YouTube video page for “Top 5 Silliest Animal Moments” (BBC Earth), extracts the description, and scans for bird names to identify the species mentioned.
- Run the script exactly as-is and share its printed output so I can confirm the exact bird species.

Python script (run as is):
```python
# Python script to determine the bird species in the BBC Earth YouTube video
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import urllib.parse
import re

headers = {
    "User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/112.0.0.0 Safari/537.36",
}

query = "BBC Earth Top 5 Silliest Animal Moments"
search_url = "https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=" + urllib.parse.quote(query)

sess = requests.Session()
resp = sess.get(search_url, headers=headers, timeout=15)
resp.raise_for_status()
soup = BeautifulSoup(resp.text, "html.parser")

video_href = None
for a in soup.find_all("a", href=True):
    href = a["href"]
    if href.startswith("/watch?v="):
        video_href = href
        break

if not video_href:
    raise SystemExit("Could not locate a YouTube watch link from search results.")

video_url = "https://www.youtube.com" + video_href
resp2 = sess.get(video_url, headers=headers, timeout=20)
resp2.raise_for_status()
soup2 = BeautifulSoup(resp2.text, "html.parser")

desc = None
# Common place YouTube puts description
m = soup2.find("meta", attrs={"name": "description"})
if m and m.get("content"):
    desc = m["content"]

if not desc:
    m = soup2.find("meta", attrs={"property": "og:description"})
    if m and m.get("content"):
        desc = m["content"]

# If still not found, try to extract from the first page text as a fallback
if not desc:
    text = soup2.get_text(" ", strip=True)
    m2 = re.search(r"Description\s*[:\-]?\s*(.*)", text, re.IGNORECASE)
    if m2:
        desc = m2.group(1)

if not desc:
    print("Description not found; cannot determine bird species from metadata.")
    desc = ""

desc_lc = (desc or "").lower()

bird_names = [
    "parrot","macaw","cockatoo","cockatiel","budgerigar","budgie","puffin","penguin",
    "owl","eagle","hawk","falcon","crow","raven","sparrow","finch","canary",
    "geese","goose","swan","pelican","flamingo","toucan","kingfisher","heron","crane",
    "parakeet","lovebird","nuthatch","grackle","tit","wren","quail","ibis","skua",
    "magpie","jay","sandpiper","dove","pigeon","crowboar"  # minor variants
]

found = [name for name in bird_names if name in desc_lc]
print("Birds mentioned in video description:", found)

if not found:
    print("No bird species detected in the description.")
else:
    print("Detected bird species (possible):", ", ".join(found))
```
